pageType: content
background:
  type: solid
  color: "$background"
elements:
  - elementId: sec-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 50, 120, 24]
    content:
      fontSize: 13
      fontFamily: "QuattrocentoSans"
      color: "#0F3D354D"
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>01 / 10</p>

  - elementId: eyebrow
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 80, 200, 24]
    content:
      style: "$eyebrow"
      color: "$primary"
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>THE PRODUCT</p>

  - elementId: heading
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 120, 480, 120]
    content:
      style: "$sectionHeading"
      text: |
        <p>What Assembly<br><em style="color:#6E8F8B;">Actually Sells</em></p>

  - elementId: body-text
    elementType: text
    bounds: [80, 260, 480, 180]
    content:
      style: "$body"
      fontSize: 18
      lineHeight: 1.6
      text: |
        <p>Assembly is a D2C luggage brand targeting India's mid-premium segment. Born post-COVID, the brand positioned itself as the design-forward alternative between mass-market VIP and premium Mokobara — offering 50% design, 50% functionality at ₹4,000–6,000.</p>

  - elementId: unit-title-bg
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [80, 460, 480, 36]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"

  - elementId: unit-title
    elementType: text
    bounds: [96, 460, 448, 36]
    content:
      fontSize: 12
      fontFamily: "QuattrocentoSans"
      color: "#FFFFFF99"
      letterSpacing: 1.5
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>UNIT ECONOMICS — ₹5,000 BAG (NSP)</p>

  - elementId: unit-bg
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [80, 496, 480, 96]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "#FFFFFF"
    border:
      style: solid
      width: 1
      color: "$border"

  # Unit row - all values and labels in one text block to avoid overlap
  - elementId: unit-row
    elementType: text
    bounds: [85, 500, 470, 88]
    content:
      fontSize: 13
      fontFamily: "SortsMillGoudy"
      color: "$text"
      lineHeight: 1.3
      align: [center, top]
      text: |
        <p><span style="color:#2E2E2E;">₹100</span>  <span style="color:#C0392B;">−₹15</span>  <span style="color:#2E2E2E;">₹85</span>  <span style="color:#C0392B;">−₹42</span>  <span style="color:#0F3D35;">₹43</span>  <span style="color:#C0392B;">−₹20</span>  <span style="color:#C0392B;">−₹20</span>  <span style="color:#6E8F8B;">₹15</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:9px; font-family:QuattrocentoSans; color:#2E2E2E66;">MRP   GST   NET   COGS   MARGIN   SHIP   MKTG   CONTRIB</span></p>

  # RIGHT COLUMN — VP Grid
  - elementId: vp1-bg
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [600, 80, 300, 260]
    shapeName: roundRect
    adjustments: [3000]
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "#FFFFFF"
    border:
      style: solid
      width: 1
      color: "$border"

  - elementId: vp1-icon
    elementType: icon
    bounds: [624, 100, 28, 28]
    iconName: "fas:industry"
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"

  - elementId: vp1-head
    elementType: text
    bounds: [624, 138, 252, 32]
    content:
      style: "$cardHeading"
      fontSize: 22
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Indian Supply Chain</p>

  - elementId: vp1-body
    elementType: text
    bounds: [624, 174, 252, 148]
    content:
      style: "$cardBody"
      fontSize: 15
      lineHeight: 1.5
      text: |
        <p>Made in India — lower COGS vs Chinese imports, a genuine competitive moat that was never positioned as a brand story.</p>

  - elementId: vp2-bg
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [920, 80, 300, 260]
    shapeName: roundRect
    adjustments: [3000]
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "#FFFFFF"
    border:
      style: solid
      width: 1
      color: "$border"

  - elementId: vp2-icon
    elementType: icon
    bounds: [944, 100, 28, 28]
    iconName: "fas:palette"
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"

  - elementId: vp2-head
    elementType: text
    bounds: [944, 138, 252, 32]
    content:
      style: "$cardHeading"
      fontSize: 22
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Minimalist Design</p>

  - elementId: vp2-body
    elementType: text
    bounds: [944, 174, 252, 148]
    content:
      style: "$cardBody"
      fontSize: 15
      lineHeight: 1.5
      text: |
        <p>Clean aesthetic, grey palette, USB ports, laptop compartments. Functional design without visible lifestyle cues.</p>

  - elementId: vp3-bg
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [600, 360, 300, 260]
    shapeName: roundRect
    adjustments: [3000]
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "#FFFFFF"
    border:
      style: solid
      width: 1
      color: "$border"

  - elementId: vp3-icon
    elementType: icon
    bounds: [624, 380, 28, 28]
    iconName: "fas:tag"
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"

  - elementId: vp3-head
    elementType: text
    bounds: [624, 418, 252, 32]
    content:
      style: "$cardHeading"
      fontSize: 22
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Right Price Point</p>

  - elementId: vp3-body
    elementType: text
    bounds: [624, 454, 252, 148]
    content:
      style: "$cardBody"
      fontSize: 15
      lineHeight: 1.5
      text: |
        <p>₹4,000–6,000 segment — same as Nasher Miles, 40% below Mokobara, 80% below Samsonite. Price bracket validated.</p>

  - elementId: vp4-bg
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [920, 360, 300, 260]
    shapeName: roundRect
    adjustments: [3000]
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "#FFFFFF"
    border:
      style: solid
      width: 1
      color: "$border"

  - elementId: vp4-icon
    elementType: icon
    bounds: [944, 380, 28, 28]
    iconName: "fas:truck"
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"

  - elementId: vp4-head
    elementType: text
    bounds: [944, 418, 252, 32]
    content:
      style: "$cardHeading"
      fontSize: 22
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>D2C + Marketplace</p>

  - elementId: vp4-body
    elementType: text
    bounds: [944, 454, 252, 148]
    content:
      style: "$cardBody"
      fontSize: 15
      lineHeight: 1.5
      text: |
        <p>60% through Amazon/Flipkart. First breakeven month achieved Oct 2023 — positive unit economics before brand equity.</p>
